TITLE: Josh Hawley unveils bill to stop Chinese corporations, CCP-linked entities from buying US farmland
SUMMARY: Missouri Sen. Josh Hawley told Fox News Digital that "no Chinese corporation or individual associated with the CCP should be permitted to own American farmland."

TITLE: Closing statements set Tuesday in OH corruption trial of former house speaker, lobbyist
SUMMARY: Closing statements are set Tuesday in an Ohio corruption trial where two Republicans are charged with conspiracy to participate in a racketeering enterprise.

TITLE: Biden admin weighs revival of policy to detain migrant families amid southern border crisis: reports
SUMMARY: The Biden administration is reportedly considering the revival of a policy that would detain migrant families who cross the southern border illegally.

TITLE: Supreme Court denies petition from Florida city to toss atheists' First Amendment suit over prayer vigil
SUMMARY: The U.S. Supreme Court on Monday handed atheists a temporary win by rejecting a the City of Ocala, Florida's request to toss a lawsuit over a prayer vigil.

TITLE: California Gov. Newsom took 'personal trip' to Baja California during devastating winter storms
SUMMARY: California Gov. Gavin Newsom, who faced criticism for leaving the state last week during record-breaking winter storms, has returned from Baja California, Mexico, his office says.

TITLE: OK residents to vote on legalizing recreational marijuana Tuesday
SUMMARY: Oklahoma voters will decide whether the state should legalize recreational marijuana Tuesday. If approved, those over 21 years old would be able to use it.

TITLE: The plane truth: Anti-global warmers Buttigieg, Biden, Kerry all questioned about jet use
SUMMARY: Biden and top officials are surrounded by scandal regarding private plane use, despite being one of the most “progressive” administrations and purporting to be hyper climate cautious.

TITLE: DHS agency appears to be 'burying' evidence of involvement with 'domestic censorship activities': expert
SUMMARY: An agency in the Department of Homeland Security appears to be "burying" evidence of its alleged censorship, according to experts and watchdog groups.

TITLE: Elon Musk torches House Jan. 6 committee for 'misleading the public,' withholding evidence: 'deeply wrong'
SUMMARY: Twitter CEO Elon Musk sharply condemned members of the House Jan. 6 Committee after Fox News host Tucker Carlson released new, never-seen-before footage from the riot.

TITLE: Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin makes unannounced visit to Iraq
SUMMARY: Defense Secretary Lloyd Austin made an unannounced trip to Iraq on Tuesday to show a U.S. commitment to maintaining its military presence in the region.

TITLE: DeSantis aiming for more conservative legislative victories in Florida while hitting trail across country
SUMMARY: Florida Gov. Ron DeSantis ready to push his conservative agenda in the state's legislative session while traveling across the country in a tour that's sparking more 2024 speculation

TITLE: Leaked Biden admin 'energy security' memo could torpedo key Biden nominee
SUMMARY: President Biden's nominee for a high-ranking Interior Department post is in serious jeopardy after an internal memo showed her prioritizing the climate agenda over energy security.

TITLE: Former Vice President Mike Pence files motion to block Jan. 6 subpoena: reports
SUMMARY: Former Vice President Mike Pence reportedly filed to block a subpoena for him to provide testimony in Special Counsel Jack Smith's investigation into the Jan. 6 capitol riot.

TITLE: Ben Savage of 'Boy Meets World' officially launches congressional campaign to replace Adam Schiff
SUMMARY: "Boy Meets World" star Ben Savage announced Monday he would be running for Congress to replace Rep. Adam Schiff, D-Calif., who is running for U.S. Senate.

TITLE: DOD still probing causes of ‘Havana syndrome’ after intelligence officials say no adversary linked: report
SUMMARY: The U.S. Defense Department says it will still continuing to investigating incidents of "Havana Syndrome" despite the intelligence community's inability to link a foreign adversary.

TITLE: Is California taxed less than Texas? New study says yes...but there's a catch
SUMMARY: Blue states like California, Massachusetts, and DC have been listed as having a lower tax rate than red states like Texas, Indiana, and Oklahoma in a new WalletHub study.

TITLE: White House mocks Marianne Williamson's run for president with 'crystal ball' joke: 'If I could feel her aura'
SUMMARY: White House press secretary Karine Jean-Pierre mocked spiritual adviser Marianne Williamson's presidential campaign on Monday with "crystal ball" and "aura" jokes.

TITLE: Kamala Harris, telling childhood story, says she asked her mom why conservatives are ‘bad’
SUMMARY: Vice President Kamala Harris said she once asked her mother why conservatives are bad, as she couldn't reconcile the political label with conservation.

TITLE: Texas state representative introduces bill to vote on secession
SUMMARY: The bill allows Texas to explore the possibility of secession and present plans to the state legislature. If passed, the referendum will be placed on the ballot in 2024.

TITLE: Southern Poverty Law Center lawyer arrested, charged with domestic terrorism amid Atlanta 'Cop City' attack
SUMMARY: A lawyer for the Southern Poverty Law Center was reportedly arrested and charged with domestic terrorism in connection to the violence that broke out in Atlanta over "Cop City."

TITLE: GOP erupts after Americans missing in Mexico: 'Cartels couldn’t ask for a better partner in crime than' Biden
SUMMARY: Republicans are pointing the finger at President Biden's border policies after four Americans were kidnapped in Mexico Friday after crossing the border from Texas.

TITLE: Wisconsin Supreme Court candidates to debate March 21
SUMMARY: Judges Janet Protasiewicz and Dan Kelly have agreed to a March 21 televised debate in a competitive race for a Wisconsin Supreme Court seat that has garnered national attention.

TITLE: Biden trips going up Air Force One steps again, second time in two weeks
SUMMARY: President Biden appeared to stumble while boarding Air Force One on Sunday, his second time having trouble trying to climb the stairs of his plane in less than two weeks.

TITLE: Jordan subpoenas former 'Disinformation Governance Board' czar Nina Jankowicz, NSBA officials for deposition
SUMMARY: House Judiciary Committee Chairman Jim Jordan subpoenaed Nina Jankowicz—the former chief of the Biden administration’s “Disinformation Governance Board”—to appear for deposition before the panel.

TITLE: Bad news for Biden: New survey shows majority of Americans more worried about inflation than taxes
SUMMARY: 81% of Americans are more concerned with inflation than with taxes and 73% do not believe taxes are being used well in a worrying sign for President Joe Biden.
